The paper deals with compressed sensing, which is a topic in information theory (cs.IT) and signal processing (cs.SP). The concept of blind compressed sensing is related to machine learning (cs.LG) and multimedia (cs.MM), as it aims to recover signals without prior knowledge of the sparsity basis. The paper also mentions simulations involving image signals, which falls under computer vision (cs.CV).
